Interactive play mode was tested with ./play.

Final selected experiment model: gomoku_pipeline_e10.bin, copied locally to gomoku_nn.bin for interactive testing.

Compared with the original random-training model, this version is more interactive and has stronger tactical benchmark performance. It can sometimes respond near human line-building threats.

However, manual play is still not reliable. In human-vs-model games, the model can still miss obvious horizontal or vertical threats and allow the human player to win directly.

Final observation:
- Automatic tactical benchmark improved.
- Manual play did not consistently improve enough.
- The current MLP-based model can learn some tactical correlations, but it still does not reliably understand 15x15 Gomoku spatial patterns.
